******
[1] Global update as of 4 Jan 2023: WPV1 ES (Afghanistan), cVDPV1 AFP (DR Congo), ES (Madagascar), cVDPV2 AFP (Algeria, Central African Republic), cVDPV2 ES (Sudan)
Date: Wed 4 Jan 2023
Source: Global Polio Eradication Initiative/WHO [edited]
https://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/this-week/


Poliovirus Weekly Update 4 Jan 2023, World Health Organization
--------------------------------------------------------------
New wild poliovirus isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 0
Environment: 3
Others: 0

New cVDPV isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 15
Environment: 15
Others: 2

Headlines
• "The mother was complaining that her son was weak and that the weakness had happened suddenly, so I examined his leg," said Spogmai. "I saw that the limb was paralysed and immediately notified the clinic's AFP focal point." [read more at https://polioeradication.org/news-post/in-afghanistan-communities-keep-an-eye-out-for-polio-in-one-of-the-viruss-last-frontiers/]

Summary of new polioviruses this week:
- Afghanistan: 3 WPV1 positive environmental samples
- Algeria: 1 cVDPV2 case
- Central African Rep: 1 cVDPV2 case and 1 CVDPV2 positive environmental sample
- DR Congo: 2 cVDPV1 cases, 11 cVDPV2 cases and 2 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples
- Madagascar: 11 cVDPV1 positive environmental samples
- Sudan: 1 cVDPV2 positive environmental sample

Afghanistan
• No wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) cases were reported this week. There are 2 cases in 2022.
• 3 WPV1 positive environmental samples were reported in Nangarhar bringing the total number of WPV1 positive environmental samples in 2022 to 20.

Pakistan
• No wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) cases were reported this week. There are 20 cases reported in 2022.

Algeria
• No circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) positive environmental sample was reported this week. The total number of positive environmental samples remains 17.
• 1 case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported in Ouargla bringing the number of cases in 2022 to 2.

Benin
• No cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported this week. There are 10 cases reported in 2022.

Botswana
• No circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 2 positive samples reported in 2022.

Burkina Faso
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 2 cases reported in 2021.

Cameroon
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There is one case reported in 2022.

Central African Republic
• 1 case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported in Région Sanitaire 6 making it the 4th case reported in 2022.
• 1 cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported in Région Sanitaire 7.

Chad
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 25 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2022.

Congo (Republic of)
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 2 cases reported in 2021.

Côte d'Ivoire
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were no cases reported in 2021.

Djibouti
• No circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) positive environmental samples were reported this week.

Democratic Republic of the Congo (DR Congo)
• 11 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported; 1 in Haut Katanga, 2 in Haut Lomami and 8 in Tanganyika, bringing the total number of cVDPV2 cases in 2022 to 221.
• 2 cVDPV1 cases were reported in Haut Lomami bringing the number of cVDPV1 cases in 2022 to 51.
• 2 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples were reported in Haut Katanga.
• Outbreak response to both cVDPV1 and cVDPV2 is being intensified.

Egypt
• No circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 18 positive samples reported in the country in the last 2 years.

Ethiopia
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There is 1 case reported in 2022.

Eritrea
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There is 1 case in 2022 and 1 case reported in 2021.

Gambia
• No circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) positive environmental samples were reported this week. There were 9 positive samples in 2021.

Ghana
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cases in 2022.

Guinea
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 6 cases in 2021.

Guinea-Bissau
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cases in the country which are linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria in 2021.

Israel
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 3 (cVDPV3) was reported this week. There is 1 case reported in 2022.
• The country has been confirmed as affected by both cVDPV2 and cVDPV3.

Indonesia
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There is 1 case reported in the country this year [2022].

Liberia
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 3 cVDPV2 cases in 2021.

Madagascar
• No cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) were reported this week. There are 13 cases in 2022. There were also 13 cases in 2021.
• 11 cVDPV1 positive environmental samples were reported; 7 in Analamanga and 4 in Sud-Ouest.

Malawi
• No case of wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) was reported this week. 1 case from 2021 has been reported this year [2022].
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) was reported this week. There are 3 cases in the country.
• Malawi continues to participate in the multi-country, sub-regional outbreak response, to urgently stop the WPV1 outbreak affecting the area.

Mauritania
• No circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) positive environmental sample was reported this week. There were 7 positive samples linked to the Jigawa outbreak in 2021.

Mozambique
• No wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) case was reported this week. There are 8 cases reported in 2022. Reporting of these new cases within a short time span indicates that intensified surveillance efforts are working in the province.
• No cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) were reported this week. There are 18 cases in 2022.
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. The number of cases in 2022 remains 4. There were 2 cases reported in 2021.

Niger
• No cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported this week. There are 13 cases in 2022. There were 18 cases reported in 2021.

Nigeria
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 42 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2022.

Senegal
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 17 cases reported in 2021.

Sierra Leone
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 5 cases reported in 2021.

Somalia
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 4 cases reported in 2022. There was 1 case reported in 2021.

Sudan
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There is 1 case reported in 2022.
• 1 cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported in West Darfur.
• Both viruses reported this year [2022] are linked to the Zamfara emergence from Nigeria.

South Sudan
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 9 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2021.

Togo
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases in 2022.
• No circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 2 positive samples reported in 2022.

Uganda
• No circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) positive environmental sample was reported this week. There were 2 positive samples linked to the N'Djamena outbreak in Chad reported in 2021.

Ukraine
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There were 2 cases reported in 2021.
• Disease surveillance continues to be strengthened, to the degree possible given the evolving situation, including by building capacity, conducting training, implementing environmental surveillance and supporting routine immunization.

United Kingdom
• No circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) positive environmental samples were reported this week. 2 positive samples were reported in May [2022] and 1 in August [2022] following the isolation of vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (VDPV2) from environmental samples in London, UK.
• No cases of paralysis associated with this strain have been detected -- virus has been isolated only from environmental (sewage) samples.

United States of America
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. 1 cVDPV2 case was reported in New York, with onset of paralysis on 20 Jun 2022.

Yemen
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 159 cases reported in 2022.

Zambia
• No circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) positive environmental sample was reported this week. There is 1 positive sample reported in 2022.

Officially reported WPV1 and cVDPV cases as of 3 Jan 2023
Wild poliovirus (WPV)
- Total global WPV1 cases in 2022: 30 (compared with 5 for the same period in 2021)
- Total global WPV1 cases in 2021: 6
Circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus (cVDPV) cases
- Total global cVDPV cases in 2022: 581 (compared with 581 for the same period in 2021)
-Total global cVDPV cases in 2021: 698

--
Communicated by:
ProMED

[In the past week, 6 countries have documented poliovirus circulation in their countries, either through acute flaccid paralysis cases with documented poliovirus isolation, or through positive environmental samples -- with indication there are infected individuals in the environmental catchment area. Poliovirus isolates during the past week included 3 wild poliovirus type 1 isolates in environmental samples in Pakistan. Circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) was isolated in AFP cases in Algeria and the DR Congo, and in environmental samples in Madagascar. And cVDPV2 has been isolated in AFP cases in the DR Congo and in ESs in Sudan. Note that all of the AFP cases and positive ESs occurred in 2022.

There was no further information available on the wastewater samples positive for VDPV2 in Canada (see Poliomyelitis update (01): (Canada) VDPV2, wastewater, RFI 20230102.8707576).

A map showing the location of each confirmed case of polio worldwide in the past 12 months can be found at https://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/. One can see cases of cVDPV in a band across Africa and in Israel, Ukraine, Tajikistan, Afghanistan, and Pakistan; cVDPV1 in DR Congo, Madagascar, Mozambique and Yemen; and WPV1 in Afghanistan, Pakistan, Malawi, and Mozambique. - Mod.MPP]

******
[2] Pakistan: violence
Date: Thu 5 Jan 2023
Source: Washington Post [edited]
https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/attackers-wound-5-pakistani-policemen-guarding-polio-workers/2023/01/05/b84bd168-8cff-11ed-b86a-2e3a77336b8e_story.html


Attackers armed with guns and hand grenades ambushed a police van assigned to guard polio workers in northwestern Pakistan, wounding 5 policemen, authorities said. Police returned fire after coming under attack near a bridge in Dera Ismail Khan, a district in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province, according to local police chief Aman Ullah.

The police chief, who was traveling with the convoy to a nearby vaccination site, said between 6 to 8 suspected militants ambushed them, opened fire and threw hand grenades at the police van.

No group claimed responsibility for the attack but Islamic militants often target polio teams and police protecting them, falsely claiming the vaccination campaigns are a Western conspiracy to sterilize children. The latest anti-polio campaign started this week, the 1st in 2023. In late November [2022], a Taliban suicide bomber blew himself up near a truck carrying police officers on their way to protect polio workers in the southwestern city of Quetta. A police officer in the truck was killed, as were 3 members of a family traveling in another car next to the truck. The Pakistani Taliban claimed the 30 Nov 2022 attack. A month earlier, in October [2022], gunmen riding on a motorcycle shot and killed a police officer assigned to guard a polio vaccination team in southwestern Baluchistan province.

Pakistan, which along with neighboring Afghanistan [are] the only [countries] where polio remains endemic, regularly launches vaccination campaigns. The latest, 5-day campaign started this week in northwestern Pakistan and is the 1st in 2023.

Since last April [2022], Pakistan has registered 20 new polio cases -- all in the northwest, where parents often refuse to inoculate children. The outbreak has been a blow to the government efforts aimed at eradicating the disease.

[Byline: Riaz Khan]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED

[The violence against polio vaccination workers including police officers protecting the actual vaccination teams is hard to fathom. In addition to the injured and killed individuals, in the long run the children suffer as seen by the increase in AFP cases associated with WPV1 infection during 2022.

A map of Pakistan with districts and provinces can be seen at https://reliefweb.int/map/pakistan/pakistan-districts-map-03-december-2018. - Mod.MPP]
